&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;B Capital is seeking a Vice President/Director to join our &lt;strong&gt;Capital Formation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;team, reporting to the Managing Director, Capital Formation. This is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;fundraising role&lt;/strong&gt;, responsible for building relationships with strategic investors and raising capital &amp;nbsp;across funds and co-investments. The ideal candidate has a proven track record of raising capital for private funds or private companies and can translate ideas into action in a fast‑moving, entrepreneurial environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Originate, drive, and close new LP commitments across institutional, family office, wealth management, and high‑net‑worth channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full fundraising cycle: mapping the universe of prospects, sourcing and nurturing relationships, leading outreach, and coordinating diligence through to close.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the MD of Capital Formation, Investor Relations team and investment leadership to refine fund positioning and tailor messages to different LP segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and customize fundraising materials (presentations, data room content, DDQs, RFPs, track‑record and portfolio analyses) in support of capital‑raising efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a high‑quality pipeline and CRM discipline, including tracking interactions, feedback, and probability‑weighted opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage and deepen relationships with gatekeepers and intermediaries (consultants, private banks, placement agents, and other capital partners) to expand the firm’s reach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent B Capital at LP meetings, conferences, and industry events, serving as a credible, front‑line fundraiser for the platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASIC JOB REQUIREMENTS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6–10 years of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;capital‑raising experience&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in venture capital, private equity, private credit, or adjacent alternatives, ideally in one or more of the following:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fundraising/capital formation at a PE/VC or alternative investment manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fundraising at a placement agent firm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Private company fundraising or private capital advisory at an investment bank or a leading private tech company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience raising capital from Endowments, Foundations, Pension Funds, Funds of Funds, Wealth Managers, and/or Family Offices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS/BA degree required; MBA or other advanced degree preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project‑management skills and comfort running multiple fundraising processes in parallel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to synthesize complex information for sophisticated institutional audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High degree of professionalism, judgment, and discretion in handling LP relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role can be based in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;San Francisco or Los Angeles&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in technology investing and/or keen interest in technology is highly desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY COMPETENCIES:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has a passion for startups, macroeconomics, and capital markets, and brings a high EQ, service oriented mindset to the team. They should:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring an existing, relevant LP network and a demonstrated ability to open doors and convert interest into commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
